OMENKA Uzoma Day aka Uzo, the former business manager of the late reggae legend, Majek Fashek, has said that he is working assiduously to shut down the popular 02 Arena in London with his brand of music. “London seems to be an open door for a lot of Nigerian artists because someone like Wizkid that has shut down O2 for three days, Burna Boy, and my brother, Davido have opened the door for more Nigerian artists to hone their trade to a universal audience. This time, it is going to be my turn. On this tour, I will be at Oxford, London city, Birmingham, Leicester, and Colchester.”   Kemi Oyedeji speaks on new book, ushering     I’m happy to be back after 10 years, says Shan George     Standing out in saturated music industry is challenging,…   Omenka, who is CEO, Miracle Day Music, recently returned from a tour of Istanbul, Turkey, and South Africa. He also said he is already preparing for another round of tours (Meet and Greet) that will take him around England. Hinting about his forthcoming plans, he said: “First, I want to thank my fans and that of Majek Fashek for their support of Miracle Day Music being the homes of superstars. We have a lot of artists like Acho, Shade Andrews, Peter De Rock Uwaifo, among others coming out soon, even King Wadada who won KORA award was on my label back in the day. “After the death of our legend Majek, I decided to take the bull by the horns to give our fans good music, live performances. We want to also thank the promoters in Europe that have been giving us tours, moving around everywhere, and their belief in good music.